# <type>: <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat (new feature)
# * fix (bug fix)
# * docs (documentation)
# * style (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
# * refactor (refactoring production code)
# * test (adding tests, refactoring test; no production code change)
# * chore (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
# * perf (performance improvements)
# * ci (continuous integration related)
# * build (build system or external dependencies)
# * revert (reverting a previous commit)
#
# Subject should use imperative mood and not end with period
# Examples:
# - feat: add interactive product viewer
# - fix: resolve mobile navigation issue
# - docs: update installation instructions
#
# Body should explain what and why vs. how
# Can be multiple paragraphs, each separated by blank line
#
# Footer should contain any BREAKING CHANGES or issue references
# Examples:
# - Closes #123
# - Fixes #456
# - BREAKING CHANGE: remove deprecated API